<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 9:35PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Beaver
and northeastern Texas Counties through 1015 PM CDT...
At 935 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northeast of Turpin, or 8 miles southeast of Liberal, moving
east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Tyrone, Forgan, Baker, Mocane, Turpin and Floris.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Oklahoma.</instruction>
